Actions.Text:
set theClipboard to the clipboard as text
log "Clipboard content: " & theClipboard

-- Define the Unicode Replacement Character (U+FFFC) literally.
set unicodeReplacementChar to (character id 65532) as text

-- Construct the Perl regular expression.
-- It looks for a markdown link where the URL part can be:
--   - Empty: ()
--   - Containing only whitespace: (   )
--   - Containing the Unicode Replacement Character (U+FFFC): (￼)
--   - Containing whitespace and the Replacement Character: ( ￼ )
-- The regex `\\[.*?\\]\\(\\s*(?:` & unicodeReplacementChar & `)?\\s*\\)`
--   - `\\[` and `\\]`: Match literal square brackets for the link text.
--   - `.*?`: Match any characters non-greedily for the link text.
--   - `\\(` and `\\)`: Match literal parentheses for the URL part.
--   - `\\s*`: Match zero or more whitespace characters.
--   - `(?:` & unicodeReplacementChar & `)?`: Match the literal U+FFFC character zero or one time (optional, non-capturing group).
set perlRegex to "\\[.*?\\]\\(\\s*(?:(" & unicodeReplacementChar & "))?\\s*\\)"

log "Perl Regex Pattern: " & perlRegex

-- Execute the Perl command to check for a match.
-- -CSD flags enable comprehensive Unicode support.
-- The clipboard content is passed as an argument using 'quoted form' for safe shell handling.
set shellCommand to "perl -CSD -e 'print \"empty\" if ($ARGV[0] =~ /" & perlRegex & "/);' -- " & quoted form of theClipboard
log "Shell Command: " & shellCommand

try
    set matchResult to (do shell script shellCommand)
    log "Shell Command Result: '" & matchResult & "'"
    
    if matchResult is equal to "empty" then
        log "Match found: Returning 'empty'"
        return "empty"
    else
        log "No match found."
    end if
on error errMsg number errNum
    log "Error executing shell command: " & errMsg & " (Error " & errNum & ")"
end try

ElseActions.Text:
This macro requires an installation of MultiMarkdown at:

/usr/local/bin/multimarkdown

To install with brew in Terminal.app, use the incantation:

    brew install multimarkdown
